# Testing Priority

**Prefer integration and component tests over unit tests.**

- Unit tests are more fragile (mocks, internals) and carry less value.
- Integration/component tests exercise real flows and give higher confidence.
- When adding coverage, add integration tests first; add unit tests only when they add clear value (e.g., complex logic, edge cases).
